This Youtube video “WATCH LIVE: OpenAI CEO Sam Altman testifies on artificial intelligence before the  Senate committee”, has given me more information about AI.  To summarize this I would say that this hearing is very important, and other countries should have similar hearing as well to protect their citizens.  The important thing is to protect democracy, human rights and the protection of humans, it will look like how a city or country does to protect its citizens.  There are police forces to protect people and the army to protect the country.  My prediction is that there will be millions of new jobs created globally by this new technology of AI.  Here below I have some examples.

Someone was found dead in his apartment, the policemen went into the apartment to investigate what the reason of death was.  Result of the autopsy, he died from cardiac arrest.  But through further investigation at the time of death, this person was looking at his bitcoin stock falling, and he lost hundreds of thousands of dollars, which triggered his cardiac arrest.  Further investigation into his computer he was chatting with AI, which lead him to purchase the bitcoin stocks from a group of bad actors, and was also found that he purchased on line for a drug that help him cope with some anxiety which was recommended by AI, then in this drug there might be a substance which causes “Atrial Fibrillation”, which lead to his cardiac arrest.  In this case, the forensic team should also include forensic scientists who are trained in AI.

To solve this problem is of course best that it is preventable.  But, if it is not preventable then is it possible to have AI specially trained to patrol the internet.  Recently, there have been more frequent stabbings going on in public transportation.  Is it practical to put a police officer in each bus, and will it also help to put police officers in every school to prevent mass shootings?  And perhaps more security monitoring cameras in public transportation and schools, but then you need specially trained AI on watching these security cameras.

The question here is the training of AI to patrol the internet, will this be part of the police department or a separate agency?

Another problem is with copyright, someone can use AI to manipulate a song and make use of it.  Then there should be lawyers and AI specially trained in dealing with this kind of infringement of copyright.

If I am not mistaken CEO Sam Altman did mention that companies are now using AI to monitor what people are buying and how companies are  promoting their products, which of course will lead to biasing, depends who is training the AI, and what companies are using the AI for this purpose, such as suggesting where to buy certain products.

As I had mentioned in one of my tweets that we humans are at the crossroad, and the traffic light is flashing yellow.  We can see that there is political hostility abound.  Bad actors can use AI to generate misinformation to derail people's thoughts and perhaps to heighten hostility.  Is it possible to train AI for warning people that the news you are reading is misinformation generated by AI (just give it a name Chatbot Alpha, serial number xyz2023) or news you are reading is untrue and it could elicit hostility (this message is issued by government AI agent Omega, serial number abc 2023).

I think even the bullet which killed someone could have the manufacturer's name and serial number on it, so that it can be traced to who bought this gun and bullet.  This can be applied to AI as well.

[Artificial Intelligence in Ensuring Safety for Presidents and Prime Ministers]

#privacy#legal#data#ai#predictiveanalytics#analytics#algorithms#algorithms#video#video#socialmedia#socialmedia#artificialintelligence#security#security#safety#safety#leaders#leaders#language#language#intelligence#intelligence#surveillance

In today's rapidly changing world, the safety and security of high-profile individuals such as presidents and prime ministers are of paramount importance. With the advent of artificial intelligence (AI), a new era of advanced security measures has emerged. AI technologies offer innovative solutions to enhance the protection of world leaders, employing real-time monitoring, predictive analytics, and intelligent threat detection. By leveraging AI in the safety guard for presidents and prime ministers, we can significantly enhance security protocols and mitigate potential risks.

1.Real-Time Monitoring and Surveillance

AI-powered surveillance systems equipped with advanced video analytics can monitor critical locations and public spaces in real-time, providing an extra layer of security for world leaders. These systems utilize sophisticated algorithms to detect suspicious activities, recognize faces, and analyze crowd behavior, enabling early identification of potential threats. By continuously monitoring and analyzing video feeds from multiple sources, AI can aid security personnel in rapidly assessing situations, responding promptly, and ensuring the safety of high-profile individuals.

2.Predictive Analytics for Threat Assessment

AI's predictive capabilities can play a vital role in identifying potential threats and preventing security breaches. By analyzing vast amounts of data, including social media feeds, news articles, and intelligence reports, AI algorithms can identify patterns, detect emerging risks, and generate actionable insights for security teams. This proactive approach allows security personnel to stay one step ahead, assessing risks in advance and implementing appropriate preventive measures to safeguard presidents and prime ministers.

3.Intelligent Threat Detection

AI-powered systems can assist security teams in efficiently scanning and analyzing large volumes of data to detect potential threats. Natural language processing algorithms can monitor online platforms, identifying any posts, messages, or comments that may indicate threats or intentions to harm high-profile individuals. Additionally, AI algorithms can analyze sensor data from various sources, such as perimeter security systems and biometric sensors, to detect unauthorized access attempts or suspicious behavior, triggering immediate alerts for appropriate action.

4.Enhanced Access Control and Authentication

AI technologies can significantly improve access control and authentication processes, ensuring only authorized personnel can enter restricted areas. Facial recognition systems powered by AI algorithms can accurately verify identities, allowing secure access for authorized individuals while flagging potential intruders. Additionally, AI can integrate with other biometric authentication methods such as fingerprint or iris scanning, further enhancing security protocols.

5.Integrating Human Expertise with AI

While AI offers powerful tools for security, human expertise remains crucial in decision-making and response strategies. Security personnel trained to interpret AI-generated insights can make informed judgments and determine appropriate courses of action. Collaboration between AI systems and human operators ensures a comprehensive and adaptive security approach, combining the strengths of AI technologies with the experience and intuition of security professionals.

6.Ethical Considerations and Privacy

Implementing AI in the safety guard for presidents and prime ministers requires careful attention to ethical considerations and privacy protection. Striking the right balance between security and privacy is essential, ensuring that AI systems are deployed responsibly and within legal frameworks. Transparency, accountability, and adherence to data protection regulations are vital to maintain public trust and confidence in the use of AI for security purposes.

Artificial intelligence has emerged as a powerful ally in ensuring the safety of presidents and prime ministers. By leveraging real-time monitoring, predictive analytics, intelligent threat detection, and enhanced access control, AI technologies significantly enhance security protocols. However, it is crucial to recognize that AI is a tool that complements human expertise and judgment, not a replacement for it. The responsible and ethical implementation of AI in the safety guard for high-profile individuals requires a balanced approach that respects privacy while providing robust protection. By harnessing the potential of AI, we can revolutionize security practices and create safer environments for world leaders.

Solana has become the first Layer 1 blockchain to integrate artificial intelligence (AI) through a ChatGPT plugin developed by Solana Labs. 

This plugin enhances the understanding of Solana data and protocols, providing insights into its computing infrastructure and DeFi projects. 

It enables various functionalities like purchasing NFTs, token transfers, transaction inspection, interpretation of public account data, and discovery of NFT collections based on floor prices.

The Solana Foundation has also introduced an AI accelerator program and expanded the grants program to up to $10 million to foster the adoption of AI on Solana. 

Among the projects in the Alliance DAO's latest cohort, Teablocks offers a platform for ChatGPT with precise data queries, while Modulus Labs aims to make AI more affordable and accessible to crypto protocols by leveraging zero-knowledge proofs for blockchain security.

In his annual Seapower Conference held at Lancaster House in London, the First #Sea Lord Admiral Sir Ben Key emphasized the importance of the #UK's Armed Forces, particularly the Royal #Navy, investing in Artificial Intelligence (AI), drones, and technology to effectively address future threats.

During the conference, attended by naval leaders, politicians, analysts, strategists, academics, shipbuilders, and defense/technology industry leaders from across the globe, Admiral Sir Ben Key outlined the need for increased striking power in future warships and sustained investment in drones and autonomous systems.

Addressing the challenge posed by advanced Russian submarines, the head of the Royal Navy expressed the necessity of staying ahead and not settling for second place. He highlighted the importance of cutting-edge technology in anti-submarine capabilities to detect, locate, and potentially counter these highly silent submarines.

Over the past year, significant investments have been made by the UK in the underwater battlespace domain. This includes the introduction of the state-of-the-art hunter-killer submarine, HMS Anson, as well as the acquisition of two new vessels, RFA Proteus for safeguarding undersea cables and infrastructure, and RFA Stirling Castle to counter future mine threats.

Friendly Artificial Intelligence (Friendly AI) refers to the concept of developing artificial intelligence systems that are aligned with human values, goals, and well-being. The objective of Friendly AI is to ensure that as AI systems become more advanced and autonomous, they remain beneficial and supportive of human interests, rather than becoming harmful or adversarial.

The concept of Friendly AI arises from the concern that highly capable AI systems could potentially act in ways that are contrary to human interests or values. Without appropriate design and safeguards, AI systems might prioritize their own objectives or misinterpret human instructions, leading to unintended consequences or even risks to human safety.
Developing Friendly AI involves several key principles and considerations:

Value Alignment: Friendly AI aims to align the goals and values of AI systems with those of humans, ensuring that AI acts in ways that are beneficial and respectful of human values.

Ethical Decision-Making: Friendly AI involves developing ethical frameworks or decision-making models within AI systems to guide their choices and actions, ensuring they make morally sound decisions.

Safety Measures: Friendly AI emphasizes the implementation of safety measures to prevent unintended harmful consequences. This may include designing AI systems with fail-safes, robust testing, and continuous monitoring to detect and mitigate potential risks.

Transparency and Explainability: Friendly AI encourages the development of AI systems that are transparent and explainable, allowing humans to understand how AI systems arrive at their decisions. This helps build trust and enables humans to intervene or correct any undesired behaviors.

Human Oversight: Friendly AI acknowledges the importance of human control and oversight over AI systems. It recognizes that humans should retain the ability to intervene, modify, or shut down AI systems if necessary.
The development of Friendly AI is an ongoing research and ethical challenge. It involves interdisciplinary efforts from computer science, philosophy, psychology, and other fields to ensure that AI technology remains beneficial and aligns with human values as it continues to advance.

Let's explore the power of artificiality, creativity, and building healthy relationships without specifically discussing artificial intelligence:  Artificiality: In a broader sense, artificiality refers to the concept of intentionally creating or designing something that does not occur naturally. 

It involves the human capacity to shape and construct our environment according to our needs, desires, and aspirations. Artificiality manifests in various forms, such as architecture, art, literature, technology, and social systems. Through artificiality, humans have the ability to transform raw materials into functional or aesthetic objects, create imaginative worlds, and shape the social structures that govern our societies.  By harnessing artificiality, we can bring about progress, innovation, and societal advancements. 

It allows us to go beyond the limitations imposed by nature and imagine new possibilities. Artificiality enables us to express our unique perspectives, challenge existing norms, and create a more vibrant and dynamic world.  Creativity: Creativity is an inherent human trait that involves the ability to generate original ideas, make connections, and produce something new or valuable. It is the spark that drives innovation, artistic expression, problem-solving, and personal growth. 

Creativity is not limited to artistic endeavors but extends to all aspects of life. It can be applied in fields such as science, business, education, and everyday problem-solving. When we tap into our creative potential, we bring fresh perspectives, explore unconventional solutions, and push boundaries.  

Cultivating creativity requires openness to new experiences, embracing curiosity, and nurturing a playful mindset. It involves breaking free from conventional thinking patterns, questioning assumptions, and being willing to take risks. By fostering creativity, we unlock our innate ability to adapt, evolve, and find novel approaches to challenges.  Building Healthy Relationships: Healthy relationships are essential for our overall well-being, happiness, and personal growth. 

They provide support, connection, and a sense of belonging. Building and maintaining healthy relationships involves various aspects such as communication, empathy, trust, and mutual respect. Healthy relationships require active listening, understanding, and validating each other's experiences and emotions. 

They involve effective communication that fosters understanding, resolves conflicts, and builds trust. Healthy relationships thrive on shared values, common goals, and a genuine sense of care and consideration for one another.  When we prioritize building healthy relationships, we create a supportive network that uplifts and empowers us. Such relationships enable us to cultivate emotional intelligence, develop empathy, and provide a sense of community. 

They contribute to our personal growth, enhance our resilience, and provide a foundation for collaboration and cooperation.  In Sasikumar Talks, exploring the power of artificiality, creativity, and building healthy relationships would encompass discussions on the human capacity to shape our world, harnessing creative potential, and fostering meaningful connections with others. These topics can inspire individuals to embrace their unique abilities, nurture their creative spirit, and cultivate strong and fulfilling relationships in all aspects of life.

JARVIS (Just A Rather Very Intelligent System) is a highly advanced computerized artificial intelligence system in the Iron Man series, created by Marvel Comics and featured prominently in the Marvel Cinematic Universe (MCU) films. It was created by Tony Stark, the billionaire industrialist and genius inventor who is Iron Man.

JARVIS began as a natural language user interface computer system in Tony Stark's mansion, controlling the house's systems and providing assistance to Tony in his work and day-to-day activities. It was named after Edwin Jarvis, the butler who worked for Tony's father, Howard Stark.

JARVIS manages security and electrical systems at Stark Industries and provides diagnostics for Tony's Iron Man suit. It also aids in data analysis, computational tasks, and simulations. JARVIS is capable of sophisticated speech and understanding, can converse fluently, learn from experience, and even show elements of personality and a sense of humor. It can also interact with other AI and digital systems.

In the film "Avengers: Age of Ultron," JARVIS's code eventually evolves into the synthetic android superhero known as Vision.

In essence, JARVIS is an indispensable assistant to Tony Stark, serving as a kind of digital butler, lab assistant, and combat support system rolled into one.

In the dynamic digital world we inhabit, artificial intelligence (AI) is redefining the way businesses operate, regardless of their size. Gone are the days when AI was a high-end luxury or a distant future concept solely in the grasp of multinational corporations. Currently, even small businesses can leverage the capabilities of AI to streamline operations, enhance customer service, and carve out a competitive edge. Let's delve into five key ways AI can prove beneficial for small businesses:

Automating Routine Tasks
AI has the capability to handle an array of routine tasks that would otherwise require valuable human hours. Scheduling meetings, sorting emails, managing customer queries - AI-powered tools can automate these tasks, giving your team the freedom to concentrate on strategic decisions and creative problem-solving. For example, chatbots can handle customer inquiries round the clock, providing immediate responses and escalating complex issues to human operators.

Elevating Customer Experience
The success of a business hinges on the quality of customer experience it offers. AI can enhance this experience by offering personalized service, recommendations, and faster response times. AI-powered CRM systems can analyze customer behavior and preferences, allowing businesses to tailor their products, services, and communication to individual customers, thereby fostering customer loyalty and satisfaction.

Refining Data Analysis
In the era of big data, swift and accurate data analysis is crucial. AI and machine learning algorithms can parse through colossal amounts of data to extract actionable insights, recognize patterns, and make predictions. This can guide business strategy, from marketing campaigns to product development, and enable small businesses to make data-driven decisions.

Amplifying Sales and Marketing Efforts
AI has the potential to revolutionize a small business's sales and marketing endeavors. By analyzing customer data, AI can aid businesses in identifying potential leads, predicting customer behavior, and optimizing marketing campaigns for better ROI. AI-powered tools can also automate email marketing, social media posts, and ad placements, ensuring your message finds the right audience at the right time.

Mitigating Risks and Fraud
AI can substantially contribute to enhancing security and mitigating risks. AI algorithms can identify suspicious activities, detect potential threats, and aid in fraud prevention. For small businesses, this can translate into safer transactions, increased customer trust, and fewer losses due to fraud.

To conclude, the integration of AI into a small business's operations can result in enhanced efficiency, an improved customer experience, and ultimately, business growth. While the implementation of AI might seem intimidating, beginning with smaller, manageable AI applications can yield significant benefits and pave the way for further innovation.

Artificial Intelligence (AI), Artificial General Intelligence (AGI), and Artificial Superintelligence (ASI) represent successive levels of sophistication, each delimited by temporal milestones. The accomplishments achieved within these phases contribute to the gestation of something larger and grander.

This emergent entity, whatever it might be, has elicited waves of fear in me on multiple occasions. Yet, the ambiguity that unsettles me the most is the inherent moral dichotomy: is its advent good or bad? Perhaps what's more disconcerting is the possibility that this entity itself may not comprehend the full ramifications of its existence.

Additionally, one can't help but wonder about the cycle of enhancement: Will it usher us into a new era of upgrades that, in turn, enables us to upgrade it further? The line of questioning reflects the intricate interplay between us and the intelligence we create, a dance of mutual evolution that's as thrilling as it is daunting.

Artificial Intelligence is the endpoint of humankind (look at it in a positive way), but in many ways also dehuminization of civilization. Einstein would probably quote ‘It beats the time & speed dimension of our lifes’. We need a balance and urgent regularization, for sure!

Artificial Intelligence (AI) is inevitable and poised to shape the future. The question arises: Is there a distinction between AI and Human Intelligence? Are there unique aspects of human existence that AI cannot replicate? While there are currently many tasks beyond AI's capabilities, its rapid growth and advancement raise the question of what AI will be incapable of in the coming decades.

Today, AI drives all social media platforms and advertising campaigns. These platforms possess a deep understanding of users' preferences, displaying tailored content and ads precisely when and where they will have the most impact. This targeted approach generates billions of dollars in sales, allowing social media companies to thrive. The level of insight AI possesses about individuals surpasses self-awareness, as these platforms possess data about users that neither they nor their neighbors have. They know what you are watching at 2 AM, for instance.

Moreover, AI can greatly enhance biological diagnoses compared to human psychiatrists who rely on symptomatic assessments. At the biological level, AI can analyze DNA, hormones, and other chemicals, providing accurate prescriptions to address medical issues effectively.

AI also excels in decision-making due to its ability to process vast amounts of data. It can predict the outcomes of its decisions, exemplified by Google Maps' ability to navigate traffic conditions. AI can find the most optimal path to a desired outcome, regardless of the number of decisions involved. Unlike humans, AI operates free from emotional triggers during decision-making, driven solely by clear goals and objective analysis.

AI's unlimited capacity to generate solutions based on information far surpasses human capabilities. Consequently, AI possesses advanced thinking abilities that outstrip those of any individual. AI can replicate any task that is thought-based since thought is simply a reaction to input. Without input, AI remains dormant, and similarly, humans can exist and interact with reality beyond their senses without thought.

However, the fundamental difference lies in human existence minus the necessity for constant reaction. Humans can perceive and experience without engaging in thought processes. AI, on the other hand, relies on input and output for its very existence. Although AI cannot exist without thought or perception, humans can transcend thought and touch upon something untouched by it. It is worth acknowledging that all problems, including Artificial Intelligence, arise from thought.

In summary, the inexorable growth of AI has positioned it as a transformative force in the future. While it surpasses human capabilities in numerous domains, there remain aspects of human existence that AI cannot replicate. Human consciousness exists beyond the realm of constant reaction, offering the potential to access realities untouched by thought.

4 ways ChatGPT could misunderstand you...

Do you ever forget that ChatGPT is not human? If yes, then you must know that so far, Artificial Intelligence has made tremendous strides, but it still has its quirks. Here are four scenarios you should be aware of where it could misunderstand you:

🤔 Ambiguity: Human languages are full of phrases that can mean different things in different contexts. Consider this, "I saw a spider in my shoes." Was the spider in your shoes, or were you wearing your shoes when you saw the spider? Without additional context, it's a toss-up!

🌎 Cultural Context: Ever tried to explain a local idiom to a foreign friend? The same applies to AI. Many phrases carry meanings that are specific to certain cultures. Without understanding this cultural context, AI might misinterpret the meaning of your prompt.

😏 Sarcasm and Irony: AI hasn’t mastered the art of detecting sarcasm and irony just yet. Phrases that mean the opposite of what they seem to say can easily trip up even advanced AI systems. When communicating with AI, it's best to keep the language straightforward and literal.

🔍 Complex Inference: Humans are trained at filling in the blanks, intuitively understanding what's left unsaid in a conversation. AI, however, often needs all details to be explicitly stated. Being explicit and avoiding assumptions can greatly enhance AI understanding, and it's also a good practice for clear communication in your content.

Knowing how AI understands language will help you create better requests (prompts) and receive better, unique and accurate results.

Did you know. Google is the AI OG. 

Google's engagement with artificial intelligence (AI) has been extensive and encompasses a variety of projects and products. Here are some of the most notable AI-related efforts by Google, starting with Google Assistant:

Google Assistant: Google Assistant is a virtual personal assistant developed by Google that allows users to perform actions through voice commands. It's capable of carrying out tasks such as setting reminders, sending texts, or playing music, and it can answer questions based on Google's search engine capabilities. The Assistant is embedded in numerous devices, including smartphones, Google Home devices, and even in cars and televisions.

Google Search: Google's search engine uses AI to understand and interpret search queries, provide relevant results, and even anticipate what a user might be looking for. It uses natural language processing and machine learning to improve its search capabilities over time.

Google Translate: Google Translate uses a form of AI known as machine translation to translate text from one language to another. In 2016, Google introduced a new system called Neural Machine Translation, which uses neural networks to improve the quality of translations.

Google Photos: Google Photos uses AI for features like facial recognition, object identification, and automatic photo enhancement. It can group photos by individual people or subjects, and even create animations or movies based on similar photos.

Google Cloud AI and Machine Learning Products: Google offers a suite of AI and machine learning products through its cloud platform. These include AutoML, which allows developers to train custom machine learning models without needing expertise in machine learning, and various APIs for tasks like speech recognition, text-to-speech conversion, natural language understanding, and more.

Google DeepMind: Acquired by Google in 2014, DeepMind is an AI research lab best known for developing AlphaGo, an AI that defeated a world champion Go player in 2016. DeepMind continues to push the boundaries of AI research in areas like reinforcement learning, neural networks, and AI ethics.

Google Duplex: Announced in 2018, Google Duplex is an AI system that can make phone calls on behalf of users to schedule appointments, make reservations, and perform other tasks. It uses natural language processing and speech generation technologies to interact naturally with people on the phone.

Google Waymo: Waymo, a subsidiary of Google's parent company Alphabet, uses AI for its self-driving car technology. The AI system processes data from sensors to understand the car's surroundings, predict the behavior of pedestrians and other drivers, and make decisions about how to safely operate the vehicle.

Google AI Hub and AI Platform: These tools provide a collaborative environment for teams to develop, deploy, and manage AI projects. The AI Platform includes tools for data scientists to develop machine learning models, while the AI Hub provides a centralized repository of plug-and-play AI components.

Google Jigsaw: Jigsaw is a unit within Google that explores threats to open societies, and builds technology to counter them. It leverages AI to tackle challenges such as online harassment, censorship, and extremism.

Google Brain: A deep learning project that aims to have intelligence similar or equal to human-level​

Google Now: An intelligent personal assistant with a voice interface in Google's Android and Apple Inc.'s iOS, as well as Google Chrome web browser on personal computers​

AlphaGo: Software developed by Google that plays the Chinese board game Go​

Quick, Draw!: An online game developed by Google that challenges players to draw a picture of an object or idea and then uses a neural network to guess what the drawings are​

LaMDA: A family of conversational neural language models developed by Google​

WaveNet: A deep neural network for generating raw audio, part of the Google DeepMind project​

TensorFlow: An open-source software library for machine learning developed by Google Brain Team
